{
  "id": "rule-from-json-basic",
  "purpose": "add_rule_from_json over the committed rules.json fixture: four accepted items \u2014 a plain rule, custom_thresholds in the list form, custom_thresholds in the dict form (clause-index key '1' parsed to int, unnamed clauses defaulted, pyreason.py:996-1027), and a weights list \u2014 the fingerprint pins the four parsed rules in item order and the reason step consumes them. The fingerprint renders names/targets/clauses but neither thresholds nor weights (the accessor fingerprint's pinned shape) \u2014 the thresholds' and weights' semantic surfaces are named unobserved here and sit with type:Threshold and the annotation-function rows.",
  "runtime_class": "smoke",
  "provenance": "docs/surface.md fn:add_rule_from_json happy-basic/happy-custom-thresholds-list/happy-custom-thresholds-dict/happy-weights; pyreason.py:868-1080 at the pin; fixture harness/fixtures/rules.json",
